higher health insurance premiums via lower wages due to obesity related healthcare costs the pilot work done here will also help to develop research proposals exploring how obesity related healthcare costs are passed on to individuals and the implications of the prevalence of obesity related healthcare costs for incentives to control weight this study is a seed project for the center on the demography and economics of health and aging contact nomita divi search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
